# {{obsolete}} A person employed to empty the contents of the outside [[toilet]] (ie. human excrement) at suburban houses (and similar).  Rendered obsolete by the introduction of plumbed (ie. piped) [[sewerage]] systems.
#: ''The 'dunny' down the back yard was emptied by the council's pan man once a week.'' &mdash; Susan Marsden, essay ''Argyle, a port worker's home 19 Forbes Street Carrington New South Wales'', describing 1920s way of life there [http://www.heritage.gov.au/ourhouse/essay7.html]
